definition: abbr. for 非洲[Fei1 zhou1], Africa

sentences.english: One of our largest non-profit clients is Pact.

sentences.chinese: 本會以非盈利分配機構性質在本港註冊成立。

sentences.english: This is one of the main beliefs of the non-profit group GlobalGiving.
sentences.chinese: 這就是非盈利團體“環宇奉獻”的主要信條之一。

sentences.english: It is a non-profit organization registered with the state government of Illinois, USA.

sentences.english: University as a non-profit organization has also been incorporated into the competitive track.

sentences.english: The Open Book Alliance also will include an assortment of nonprofit groups.
sentences.chinese: 開放圖書聯盟同樣將包括各種各樣的非盈利組織。

sentences.english: These are non-profit public institutions dedicated to promoting Chinese language and culture.

sentences.english: The council is the non-profitable (a nonprofit) organization, made up of building industry leaders.

sentences.english: Other non-profits use wristbands as complements to more prominent symbols of identity.
sentences.chinese: 還有一些非盈利組織使用手環來突出自己的表示。

sentences.english: It must be a non-profit group, according to Congress.
sentences.chinese: 根據國會的議案，這個夥伴必須是非盈利組織。
